Questions that arise after the accident: Stewards in the car because they are illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden.
In the context of the tragic bus accident of the Student Agency company near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can move inside the bus during the journey.
"If one wants to strictly and formally comply with the law, the activity of a steward is contrary to the road traffic law," said Transport Ministry spokesperson Karel Hanzelka.
The accident, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the road from the bus.
The girl was sadly sitting next to the driver, on the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had two other seats at her disposal.
However, the bus may have an accident, or even slow down abruptly, even when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is under its technical file equipped with standing seats or not.
If this stand-up equipment is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
Student Agency long-distance buses do not have standing seats, which was confirmed at Aktu<0xC3><0xA1>ln<0xC4><0x9B>.cz by the company director Radim Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura.
"This is an issue that we have discussed with the department and, at first, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got the passengers to go to the toilet during the ride provided they have their own seat," he said.
The law ignores the stewards.
“There is no unequivocal legal interpretation of the role of steward – no legal prescription deals with that role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The Road Transport Act only knows the term vehicle receiver; it does not define its rights and duties," Hanzelka added with more ambiguity.
On the contrary, Josef Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, the director of the traffic department for road vehicles, believes that the law addresses the problem sufficiently.
"It all depends on whether the coach has the permission to offer standing seats in its approval.
It's all in there," he said.
Buses are divided into urban ones, where there are standing seats and a limited maximum speed, intercity ones with standing seats and a higher permissible speed and long-distance buses without standing seats with the highest permissible maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
Just like on a plane, an expert said.
Jaroslav Hor<0xC3><0xAD>n, expert at BESIP (road traffic safety) in transport, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"In regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in airplanes.
There, too, it is not certain when a turbulence will occur and the air hostess can sneeze her head."
"Now, in case the bus would have braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or in a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards through internal regulations," he says, and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the issue is not resolved.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier offering stewards services.
He hired two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their trade to be a risky trade.
"However, as soon as I have the impression that it is a risky profession, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper on board.
It would also reduce costs,” he said.
The safety concern is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of Asiana Alexei Litvine, who ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses, we've been against it from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end up in a fatal accident," he said, a year ago, in T<0xC3><0xBD>den.cz.
An immense tragedy has happened.
A young hostess from the Plze<0xC5><0x88> region, who had been working for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency strip without using a blinker and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter trying to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he frowned on his right side.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura refused to sell the two seats reserved for the stewards’ rest.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these seats, they are blocked."
The company plans to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but in terms of financial compensation, it also counts on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been in the process of being drafted for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Department of Transportation, could provide clarification on the movements of stewards on board the bus.
"Now, it has not come to any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the laptop at the wheel," says expert Hor<0xC3><0xAD>n.
"The Department of Transportation does not consider the activity of stewards to be something that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," Hanzelka said, stating that the control of the safety of buses is under the authority of the police and the Occupational Safety Office.
