In August 2008, domestic industrial sales prices increased by 0.1 per cent compared to the previous month, and by 12.9 per cent compared to the month of August 2007 - reports the Central Statistical Office of Hungary.
Industrial export sales prices increased by 1.1 per cent compared to those in July 2008, while compared to a year earlier, they decreased by 3.9 per cent.
As a result of fluctuations in domestic and export prices, industrial production prices increased by 0.7 per cent compared to the previous month, and by 3.2 per cent compared to the previous year.
Domestic industrial sales prices have increased to a lesser extent: by 0.1 percent, compared to the previous month.
Domestic sales prices in the processing industry have only experienced a slight increase in the order of 0.1 per cent compared to July.
In August 2008, the most significant price increase was observed in the leather and footwear manufacturing sector (2.8 percent), with first, the manufacture of bags and belts with a monthly increase of 4.6 percent, then, the production of shoes with a 2.5 percent monthly increase.
